search.title: Chemical reaction
search.snippet: A reaction is a process that leads to the chemical transformation of one set of chemical substances to another.

search.title: React (JavaScript library)
search.snippet: React is a free and open-source front-end JavaScript library for building web user interfaces. It is a popular software framework in web computing technology, maintained by Meta.

search.title: React Native
search.snippet: React Native is an open-source UI software framework created by Meta Platforms. It is used to develop applications for Android, iOS, and web.

search.title: Nuclear reaction
search.snippet: In nuclear physics and nuclear chemistry, a nuclear reaction is a process in which two nuclei collide to produce one or more nuclides.

search.title: Reaction (physics)
search.snippet: In physics, a reaction is a force that acts in the opposite direction to an action force.
